  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0daf\u0dd6\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba \u0db8\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dbd\u0db1  \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"The strugglers are informed how to fight corruption\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Acting President Ranil Wickramasinghe has stated in a discussion with ministers and members of parliament that the \"People's Council\" mentioned in the proposal handed over to the government by the peaceful struggle leaders is accepted as a very good plan.",
        "The Acting President has further mentioned that the activists are continuously making accusations regarding the incidents of fraud and corruption and that in the future the government will inform the activists about the measures taken to combat corruption.",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe made a statement after taking the oath of office of the Acting President and said that there is a big difference between the rebels and the strugglers. The Acting President also mentioned that many people who have been involved in the struggle since the beginning have expressed their opposition to the disruptive actions of the rebels. The real strugglers do not act violently. The Acting President also said that his belief."
      ],
      "title_ents": [],
